  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Sexual and Reproductive Health Assistance and Promotion for Women and Girl Migrants and Refugees from Venezuela and Host Communities in Colombia and Ecuador</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims at strengthening women and girls comprehensive sexual and reproductive health rights and system for migrants from Venezuela and host communities in with a sustainable people-centered approach.  The Intervention will focus on empowering women and girls from communities and institutions to promote and exercise their voice and agency related to their sexual and reproductive health rights (SRHR).  It will also focus on increasing access to comprehensive gender responsive SRHR services to women and girls and improving access to healthcare assistance and referrals, to benefit women and girl from host communities and Venezuelan migrants, survivors of gender based violence (GBV) and sexual exploitation. To achieve this, IOM will work and support government structures, strengthen the capacities of institutions and community stakeholders and will sensitize communities, and local leaderships to improve the promotion of comprehensive gender responsive SRH rights and services for all.</narrative>
  </description>
